S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
H O U S E R E S O L U T I O N
EXTENDING DEEPEST CONDOLENCES ON THE PASSING OF ROBIN ANN
MONTECALVO
Introduced By: Representatives Fascia, O'Brien, Read, Marszalkowski, Fellela,
Paplauskas, Corvese, Messier, Hull, and Blazejewski
Date Introduced: February 11, 2025
Referred To: House read and passed
1 WHEREAS, It is with sadness that this House has learned of the untimely passing of
2 Robin Ann Montecalvo, the beloved wife of Gian Montecalvo; and
3 WHEREAS, Robin Montecalvo was born in the City of Providence, a daughter of the late
4 Richard and Eileen Langevin, the sister of Gary Langevin and his wife Cristine, and Coleene
5 Golderese and her husband, Stephen, and the daughter-in-law of Phyllis A. Montecalvo; and
6 WHEREAS, In addition, Mrs. Montecalvo leaves behind her extended family, aunt and
7 uncle, Thomas and Crystal Leddy, her nephew, Nicholas Fournier, and her beloved canine
8 companions, Bosco and Reggie; and
9 WHEREAS, Upon graduation from college, Mrs. Montecalvo was employed as a
10 licensed practical nurse (LPN) for Rhode Island Hospital. She took great pride and had a deep
11 passion for the care of her patients while working as an LPN for the Visiting Nurses Association,
12 where she provided homecare. She was also a Scentsy representative for over thirteen years; and
13 WHEREAS, In addition to her work, Mrs. Montecalvo loved spending time with family
14 and friends and in her spare time, enjoyed listening to country music; and
15 WHEREAS, Robin Ann Montecalvo had an “incredibly kind heart”, “unapologetic
16 humor”, and “steadfast determination”. She was an anchor for those who were lucky to be a part
17 of her life, and she is deeply missed; now, therefore be it
18 RESOLVED, That this House of Representatives of the State of Rhode Island hereby
19 extends deepest sympathy and condolences on the passing of Robin Ann Montecalvo; and be it

1 further
2 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of State be and hereby is authorized and directed to
3 transmit a duly certified copy of this resolution to Gian Montecalvo and Family.
